  "prompt": "Can you make Bisquick pancakes without eggs?",
  "response": "Yes, you can definitely make Bisquick pancakes without eggs! While eggs are a common ingredient in pancake recipes to help with binding and leavening, you can use egg substitutes or other ingredients to achieve a similar result. Here\u2019s a simple recipe for egg-free Bisquick pancakes:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- **2 cups Bisquick mix**  \n- **1 cup milk (or a non-dairy alternative like almond, soy, or oat milk)**  \n- **1 tablespoon sugar (optional)**  \n- **1 tablespoon vegetable oil or melted butter**  \n- **1 teaspoon baking powder (optional, for extra fluffiness)**  \n- **1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional, for added flavor)**  \n\n### Instructions:\n1. In a mixing bowl, combine the Bisquick mix, sugar (if using), and baking powder (if using).  \n2. Add the milk, vegetable oil or melted butter, and vanilla extract (if using). Stir until just combined; the batter will be slightly lumpy, which is fine.  \n3. Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. Lightly grease with oil or butter.  \n4. Pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.  \n5. Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges look set, about 2-3 minutes. Flip and cook for another 1-2 minutes until golden brown.  \n6. Serve warm with your favorite toppings like syrup, fruit, or whipped cream.\n\n### Notes:\n- If the batter seems too thick, add a splash of milk to thin it out.  \n- For a vegan version, use non-dairy milk and a plant-based oil or butter substitute.\n\nEnjoy your egg-free Bisquick pancakes!",
